properties.areaDesc: Upper North Platte River Basin; Southwest Carbon County
properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 1 at 9:24AM MST until January 1 at 11:00PM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
...Winter Storm Warning Through Thursday Afternoon for the Snowy
and Sierra Madre Ranges...

...Blizzard Warning for Carbon County from Arlington to Rawlins
Through This Evening...

* WHAT...Snow. Additional snow accumulations of up to 4 inches.
Winds gusting as high as 35 mph.

* WHERE...Southwest and south central Carbon County to include
Baggs...Saratoga and Encampment.

* WHEN...Until 11 PM MST this evening.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. Patchy blowing
snow could significantly reduce visibility. The hazardous
conditions could impact the evening commute.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 11 PM MST THIS EVENING
